Lost to the Goblins x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(60)">Denizens Enraged</a>  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> This Deck is based to do two things:<br>
<br>
1.	Have a Small Fellowship to give the opponent as little room as possible to<br>
work with.<br>
<br>
2.	SWARM, SWARM, SWARM...HAHAHAHAHA<br>
<br>
<br>
To swarm is very easy just put out as much as possible and get Frodo to fight as<br>
many Orcs as possible and overwhelm him.  It must be the easiest deck ever. <br>
You can get most of your orcs from the discard pile with Host of Thousands and<br>
They are Comming, so dont worry about losing them, It works very well and it is<br>
fun to watch Frodo fight 3 goblins and die.  HAHAHAHA<br>
<br>
<br>
Now the Free People.  On turn one I use the Prancing Pony to get Aragon out. <br>
YOU MUST GO FIRST VERY IMPORTANT!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  Next use those 4 to go as<br>
far a possible a turn.  Use the Stealth cards a much as needed per turn.  Once<br>
your at site 6 your should be set.  Stop there and heal then get to site nine in two<br>
turns by whatever you have left.  Now with your Shadow deck they should not be<br>
moving that much each turn I have NEVER had someone move 2 times a turn<br>
and not had one of their guys die in the process.  <br>
<br>
When all is working for you it is a great thing, but that doesn&#8217;t always happen. <br>
Dont worry this is a good enough deck that if something goes wrong it can<br>
rebound late in the game with a overwhelming <br>
<br>
<br>
If you have any questions D-Mail me<br>
<br>
Thanks for Reading and Have fun. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20397"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20397" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
